# Server-side GitHub credential (FR-003a) — required even for local dev.
# Raises the GitHub REST API rate limit from 60/hr/IP (unauthenticated) to 5,000+/hr.
# This is a backend-only secret: it authenticates the app to GitHub, never a user.
# Create a fine-grained personal access token (no scopes needed for public repo reads)
# or a GitHub App installation token, then set it here. Never commit the real value.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
